@{
    ViewData["HeroTitle"] = "About Us";
    ViewData["HeroSubtitle"] = "Supporting mental health recovery through compassion, community, and care.";
}

<partial name="_PageHero" />

<!-- ORGANISATION OVERVIEW -->
<section class="section-light">
    <div class="content-container">

        <h2>Who We Are</h2>

        <p>
            Friends of Valkenberg Trust is a non-profit organisation dedicated to supporting
            patients at Valkenberg Hospital. Our work focuses on enhancing the recovery journey
            of individuals living with serious mental illnesses by providing resources, programs,
            and community-driven support.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4">
            Through collaboration with healthcare professionals, donors, and volunteers, we aim
            to create an environment where patients are treated with dignity, compassion, and respect.
            Our initiatives bridge the gap between clinical care and human connection.
        </p>

    </div>
</section>

<div class="card text-center">
    <p>
        "Our mission is to support recovery, restore dignity, and build a community
        around mental health care."
    </p>
</div>

<!-- WHAT WE DO -->
<section class="section-alt">
    <div class="content-container">

        <h2>What We Do</h2>

        <div class="card mt-6">
            <h3>Patient Support</h3>
            <p>
                We provide essential items, resources, and programmes that directly improve the
                quality of life for patients within Valkenberg Hospital.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card mt-6">
            <h3>Community Engagement</h3>
            <p>
                By hosting events and outreach programmes, we actively involve the broader
                community in supporting mental health awareness and reducing stigma.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card mt-6">
            <h3>Fundraising Initiatives</h3>
            <p>
                Our fundraising efforts enable us to sustain and expand the services we provide,
                ensuring long-term impact and support for those in need.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

<!-- HISTORY -->
<section class="section-light">
    <div class="content-container">

        <h2>Our History</h2>

        <p>
            Friends of Valkenberg Trust was established with the vision of improving the lives of
            patients at Valkenberg Hospital. Over the years, the organisation has grown from a small
            support initiative into a structured and impactful network of volunteers, donors, and partners.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4">
            Through consistent effort and community involvement, the Trust has played a key role in
            supplementing hospital resources and introducing programmes that promote recovery,
            dignity, and inclusion.
        </p>

    </div>
</section>

<!-- GOVERNANCE + NETWORKING -->
<section class="section-alt">
    <div class="content-container">

        <h2>Governance & Partnerships</h2>

        <div class="card mt-6">
            <h3>Governance</h3>
            <p>
                The Trust is guided by a committed board and governance structure that ensures
                transparency, accountability, and responsible management of resources. All activities
                are aligned with our mission to support mental health care and patient wellbeing.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card mt-6">
            <h3>Networking & Collaboration</h3>
            <p>
                We work closely with healthcare professionals, community organisations, and donors
                to strengthen our impact. These partnerships allow us to extend our reach and deliver
                meaningful support where it is needed most.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

<!-- REPORTS -->
<section class="section-light">
    <div class="content-container">

        <h2>Reports & Transparency</h2>

        <p>
            We believe in transparency and accountability. Our reports provide insight into our
            activities, financial management, and the impact of our work within the community.
        </p>

        <ul class="mt-6">
            <li><a href="#">Annual Report 2024</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Event Reports</a></li>
        </ul>

    </div>
</section>

<!-- CONTACT CTA -->
<section class="section-alt">
    <div class="content-container text-center">

        <h2>Get in Touch</h2>

        <p>
            Whether you are looking to support our cause, partner with us, or learn more about our work,
            we would love to hear from you.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4">Email: info@fovt.org</p>

        <a href="/Home/Contact" class="btn-donate mt-6">Contact Us</a>

    </div>
</section>